### Phase 13 UAT: Group Server & SDK
### Server must be running on localhost:8080
### Requires: a registered Admin user and a regular User

### ============================================================
### SETUP: Register an admin user (or login with existing one)
### ============================================================

### Login as Admin (adjust credentials to your admin account)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ignis.fatue@gmail.com",
  "password": "Mm.12345"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("adminRefreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### Register a regular test user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "uat-phase13-user@test.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "firstName": "UAT",
  "lastName": "User"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("userToken", response.body.accessToken);
%}

### Login as the regular user (if already registered)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "uat-phase13-user@test.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("userToken", response.body.accessToken);
%}

### ============================================================
### TEST 3: Group CRUD via API
### ============================================================

### 3a. Create a group (Admin+ required) — expect 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "UAT Test Group",
  "slug": "uat-test-group",
  "description": "Created during Phase 13 UAT"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("groupId", response.body.id);
%}

### 3b. Get group by ID — expect 200 with name, slug, description, timestamps
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{groupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3c. Update group — expect 200 with updated name
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{groupId}}/update
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "UAT Test Group (Updated)",
  "description": "Updated during Phase 13 UAT"
}

### 3d. Verify update — GET again, check name is "UAT Test Group (Updated)"
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{groupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3e. Delete group — expect 200 with "Group deleted" message
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{groupId}}/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3f. Verify delete — GET should return 404/error
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{groupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ============================================================
### TEST 4: RBAC Enforcement
### ============================================================

### Create a fresh group for RBAC tests
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "RBAC Test Group",
  "slug": "rbac-test-group",
  "description": "For RBAC verification"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("rbacGroupId", response.body.id);
%}

### 4a. Regular User cannot create groups — expect 403 Forbidden
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "name": "Should Fail",
  "slug": "should-fail",
  "description": "Regular user should not be able to create"
}

### 4b. Regular User (not a member) cannot access group — expect 403
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 4c. Add user as MEMBER to the RBAC group
### First, get user ID from /api/users/me
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

> {%
    client.global.set("testUserId", response.body.id);
%}

### Add the regular user as MEMBER
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/members/add
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "userId": "{{testUserId}}",
  "role": "MEMBER"
}

### 4d. Member CAN read group — expect 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 4e. Member CANNOT update group — expect 403
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/update
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "name": "Should Not Update"
}

### 4f. Member CANNOT delete group — expect 403
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### ============================================================
### TEST 5: Cross-Group Data Isolation
### ============================================================

### Create a second group (user will NOT be a member)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Isolated Group",
  "slug": "isolated-group",
  "description": "User should not be able to access this"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("isolatedGroupId", response.body.id);
%}

### 5a. User in RBAC group cannot access Isolated group — expect 403
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{isolatedGroupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 5b. Admin (owner of both) CAN access Isolated group — expect 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{isolatedGroupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ============================================================
### TEST: Member Management
### ============================================================

### List members of RBAC group (admin is owner + test user is member)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Remove the test user from RBAC group
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/members/{{testUserId}}/remove
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Verify removal — user can no longer access group (403)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### ============================================================
### TEST: Register Member (create new user directly into group)
### ============================================================

### Register a brand new user into the RBAC group
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/members/register
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "email": "uat-registered-member@test.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "firstName": "Registered",
  "lastName": "Member",
  "role": "MEMBER"
}

### ============================================================
### TEST: Duplicate Slug Rejection
### ============================================================

### Try to create a group with the same slug — expect error
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Duplicate Slug",
  "slug": "rbac-test-group",
  "description": "Should fail — slug already exists"
}

### ============================================================
### CLEANUP: Delete test groups
### ============================================================

### Delete RBAC test group
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{rbacGroupId}}/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Delete Isolated group
POST http://localhost:8080/api/groups/{{isolatedGroupId}}/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Logout admin
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
